#: Game.Levels.CyclicGroups
msgid "What is the simplest kind of group? One answer: a group generated\n"
"by a single element. Such groups are called **cyclic**.\n"
"\n"
"The integers В§0 (generated by В§1) and the clock group В§2\n"
"(generated by В§3) are the prototypical examples. But cyclic\n"
"groups show up in unexpected places: every group of **prime order**\n"
"is forced to be cyclic, regardless of how it was defined.\n"
"\n"
"This world introduces three key concepts:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Integer powers** В§4 вҖ” extending natural-number\n"
"   powers to negative exponents via В§5.\n"
"\n"
"2. **zpowers** В§6 вҖ” the subgroup generated by\n"
"   a single element, consisting of all integer powers of В§7.\n"
"\n"
"3. **Order** В§8 вҖ” the smallest positive В§9 such that\n"
"   В§10, measuring the \"period\" of an element.\n"
"\n"
"The gateway theorem connecting these: a group is cyclic\n"
"(В§11) exactly when some element's zpowers equals the\n"
"whole group (В§12).\n"
"\n"
"By the boss level, you'll prove that **every group of prime order\n"
"is cyclic** вҖ” the fundamental structural result that drives\n"
"classification of finite groups.\n"
"\n"
"Two new tactics appear:\n"
"- В§13 вҖ” closes goals that are computationally verifiable\n"
"- В§14 вҖ” reduces any goal to В§15 for contradiction arguments"
msgstr ""

