msgid "You've met В§0, the defining property of a commutative group.\n"
"\n"
"Notice the type signature: we wrote В§1 instead of\n"
"В§2. This tells Lean that В§3 is commutative, which makes\n"
"В§4 available. If you tried to use В§5 with only\n"
"В§6, Lean would refuse вҖ” it doesn't know the group is\n"
"commutative.\n"
"\n"
"Remember the shoes-and-socks lemma from Group Basics:\n"
"В§7, where the order *reversed*. With\n"
"В§8, you could rearrange that back to В§9 вҖ” no\n"
"reversal needed. That's the connection the earlier world promised.\n"
"\n"
"In a В§10, you can freely rearrange the order of factors.\n"
"But *which* factors you swap matters when there are more than two.\n"
"In the next level, you'll learn to direct В§11 at specific\n"
"pairs."
msgstr ""

