#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro
msgid "Welcome to **Commutative Groups**, where multiplication finally\n"
"obeys the rule you've been taking for granted since primary school:\n"
"В§0.\n"
"\n"
"Not every group is commutative. The integers under addition are,\n"
"but the group of 2-by-2 invertible matrices under multiplication\n"
"is not. A group where В§1 for all elements В§2 and В§3 is\n"
"called **abelian** (after Niels Henrik Abel) or **commutative**,\n"
"and Lean calls its type В§4.\n"
"\n"
"In a В§5, you can freely rearrange products вҖ” shuffling\n"
"factors into whatever order is convenient. This unlocks results\n"
"that fail for general groups. The headline example: if В§6 and В§7\n"
"commute, then В§8. In a non-commutative\n"
"group, this is false вҖ” try expanding В§9 in a general\n"
"group and you get В§10, which rearranges to\n"
"В§11 only if В§12.\n"
"\n"
"Along the way, you'll learn the В§13 (power) notation and the\n"
"В§14 tactic вҖ” which you already know from the Natural Number\n"
"Game, just re-introduced here for this game's inventory.\n"
"\n"
"By Level 6, you'll prove the **power-of-a-product** theorem:\n"
"\n"
"В§15\n"
"\n"
"using induction and the tools from this world."
msgstr ""

