#: Game.Levels.GroupBasics
msgid "Welcome to **Group Basics**, where you'll see the real power of the\n"
"three group axioms.\n"
"\n"
"In the Group Tutorial, you used five tools: В§0, В§1,\n"
"В§2, В§3, and В§4. But only three of\n"
"these are truly independent:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Associativity**: В§5\n"
"2. **Right identity**: В§6\n"
"3. **Right inverse**: В§7\n"
"\n"
"Everything else вҖ” left identity, left inverse, cancellation laws,\n"
"uniqueness of inverses вҖ” can be **derived** from these three. That's\n"
"what this world is about. Minimizing axioms isn't pedantry вҖ” it means\n"
"less to verify when checking that a new structure is a group.\n"
"\n"
"Along the way, you'll build a toolkit of cancellation lemmas that\n"
"make group algebra much faster than raw axiom manipulation.\n"
"\n"
"**Note**: The В§8 tactic is **disabled** for this entire world.\n"
"You need to prove everything from the axioms and the theorems you\n"
"derive. В§9 will return in the next world.\n"
"\n"
"By the end of this world, you'll prove the **shoes-and-socks lemma**:\n"
"\n"
"В§10\n"
"\n"
"вҖ” the inverse of a product is the product of the inverses in reverse\n"
"order."
