#: Game.Levels.HomBasics
msgid "Welcome to **Kernel and Image**.\n"
"\n"
"In the last world, you learned to push a homomorphism through group\n"
"operations: В§0, В§1, В§2.\n"
"You ended by showing that В§3 implies В§4.\n"
"\n"
"That calculation revealed something important: the set\n"
"В§5 captures exactly how much information\n"
"В§6 loses. Elements in the kernel are \"invisible\" to В§7 вҖ” they all\n"
"get mapped to the identity.\n"
"\n"
"The **kernel** of a homomorphism is always a subgroup: it contains В§8,\n"
"is closed under multiplication, and is closed under inverses. In Lean,\n"
"В§9 is a В§10.\n"
"\n"
"At the other end, the **range** (or image) of В§11 is the set of elements\n"
"in В§12 that В§13 actually reaches: В§14.\n"
"This is also a subgroup, written В§15.\n"
"\n"
"The central question of this world: **when does В§16 lose no information?**\n"
"A homomorphism is injective exactly when its kernel is trivial вҖ” when\n"
"В§17. If the only element that maps to В§18 is В§19 itself, then\n"
"distinct inputs always produce distinct outputs.\n"
"\n"
"You will prove both directions of this equivalence and combine them into\n"
"the boss theorem: В§20.\n"
"\n"
"Along the way, you'll learn the В§21 tactic, which lets you\n"
"pin a universal hypothesis to a specific element."
msgstr ""

