#: Game.Levels.CommGroupIntro.L06_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing **Commutative Groups**!\n"
"\n"
"You proved the **power-of-a-product** theorem by induction. The\n"
"key step was the interchange law В§0, which\n"
"rearranged В§1 into В§2.\n"
"This rearrangement is exactly where commutativity was needed вҖ” in\n"
"a non-commutative group, you cannot swap В§3 past В§4.\n"
"\n"
"Your new toolkit from this world:\n"
"\n"
"| Theorem | Statement |\n"
"|---------|-----------|\n"
"| В§5 | В§6 |\n"
"| В§7 | В§8 |\n"
"| В§9 | В§10 |\n"
"| В§11 | В§12 |\n"
"| В§13 | В§14 |\n"
"| В§15 | В§16 |\n"
"| В§17 | В§18 |\n"
"| В§19 | В§20 |\n"
"\n"
"And the re-introduced tactic: В§21.\n"
"\n"
"**Why commutativity matters**: the equation В§22\n"
"is a litmus test for commutativity. If this holds for all В§23, В§24,\n"
"and В§25, then the group must be abelian. Here's why:\n"
"expand В§26 and В§27.\n"
"Setting them equal gives В§28. Cancel\n"
"В§29 on the left and В§30 on the right to get В§31.\n"
"So a single power identity forces full commutativity. You'll see the\n"
"converse direction вҖ” measuring *how far* a group is from being abelian вҖ”\n"
"when you study commutator subgroups.\n"
"\n"
"Next up: subgroups вҖ” where you'll learn what it means for a subset\n"
"of a group to form a group in its own right."
msgstr ""

