#: Game.Levels.HomComposition.L05_CompSurjective
msgid "If В§0 is surjective, then В§1 is surjective. The argument:\n"
"for any В§2, surjectivity of В§3 gives В§4 with\n"
"В§5, so В§6 is a preimage of В§7 under В§8.\n"
"\n"
"The duality between the boss theorem and this result:\n"
"\n"
"| Hypothesis | Conclusion | Transfers to |\n"
"|------------|------------|--------------|\n"
"| В§9 injective | В§10 injective | inner map |\n"
"| В§11 surjective | В§12 surjective | outer map |\n"
"\n"
"Why the asymmetry? Think of it as a pipeline В§13:\n"
"- If nothing collides at the end (injective composition), nothing\n"
"  can collide at the start (injective В§14). But В§15 might still\n"
"  collide on elements outside В§16.\n"
"- If everything is reached at the end (surjective composition),\n"
"  everything is reached by the second step (surjective В§17). But\n"
"  В§18 might miss parts of В§19 that В§20 still covers.\n"
"\n"
"This is the **inner/outer transfer** pattern:\n"
"\n"
"| Hypothesis | Conclusion | Transfers to |\n"
"|------------|------------|--------------|\n"
"| В§21 injective | В§22 injective | inner map |\n"
"| В§23 surjective | В§24 surjective | outer map |\n"
"\n"
"Think of В§25 as a pipeline. If the pipeline never\n"
"collides (injective), the first step can't collide either. If the\n"
"pipeline reaches everything (surjective), the second step reaches\n"
"everything too.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *For any В§26, surjectivity of В§27 gives В§28\n"
"with В§29. So В§30 is a preimage of В§31 under В§32,\n"
"proving В§33 surjective.*"
msgstr ""

