#: Game.Levels.NormalDef.L09_Boss
msgid "Every kernel is a normal subgroup. This is the foundational link\n"
"between homomorphisms and quotient groups.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *Let В§0 be a homomorphism and В§1. For\n"
"any В§2:*\n"
"\n"
"*В§3*\n"
"\n"
"*so В§4. Hence В§5 is normal in В§6.*\n"
"\n"
"The **conjugation-check** move is the standard technique for proving\n"
"normality: given В§7 and В§8, show В§9 by\n"
"algebraic manipulation. For kernels, \"algebraic manipulation\" means\n"
"pushing В§10 through the expression and using В§11.\n"
"\n"
"Proof moves learned:\n"
"- **Conjugation-check**: to prove В§12, show\n"
"  В§13 for all В§14, В§15\n"
"- **Normal constructor**: В§16 + В§17\n"
"- **Kernel normality argument**: unfold В§18, push В§19 through,\n"
"  substitute В§20, cancel\n"
"\n"
"Why does normality matter? Here's the concrete reason: to multiply\n"
"cosets В§21, you need the result to be independent of\n"
"which representatives you pick. If В§22, then В§23. For this to land in В§24, you need\n"
"В§25 вҖ” which is exactly the normality condition. Without\n"
"normality, different representatives give different cosets, and\n"
"В§26 is just a set of cosets, not a group.\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: The *converse* is false вҖ” not every normal subgroup is a\n"
"kernel... unless you construct the right homomorphism. In fact, В§27 is\n"
"normal if and only if В§28 is the kernel of the natural map В§29.\n"
"That's the quotient construction you'll see later."
msgstr ""

