#: Game.Levels.HomBasics.L08_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing **Kernel and Image**!\n"
"\n"
"You proved the fundamental connection:\n"
"\n"
"> **A group homomorphism is injective if and only if its kernel is trivial.**\n"
"\n"
"Both directions:\n"
"- **ker = вҠҘ вҶ’ injective**: If В§0, then\n"
"  В§1, so В§2, so В§3.\n"
"- **injective вҶ’ ker = вҠҘ**: If В§4 and В§5 is\n"
"  injective, then В§6.\n"
"\n"
"This theorem says: **the kernel measures exactly the failure of\n"
"injectivity**. The bigger the kernel, the more information В§7 loses.\n"
"\n"
"Your tools from this world:\n"
"\n"
"| Item | Type | Purpose |\n"
"|------|------|---------|\n"
"| В§8 | Definition | Kernel subgroup: В§9 |\n"
"| В§10 | Theorem | В§11 |\n"
"| В§12 | Definition | Range subgroup: В§13 |\n"
"| В§14 | Theorem | В§15 |\n"
"| В§16 | Definition | В§17 |\n"
"| В§18 | Theorem | В§19 |\n"
"| В§20 | Tactic | Pin a universal hypothesis to a specific value |\n"
"\n"
"Proof moves:\n"
"- **Kernel reasoning**: В§21 вҶ’ algebra вҶ’ В§22\n"
"- **Image reasoning**: В§23 witness вҶ’ transform вҶ’ В§24\n"
"\n"
"The **kernel navigation diamond** summarizes the key equivalences:\n"
"\n"
"В§25\n"
"\n"
"Each arrow is one В§26 step. The forward direction of the boss\n"
"chains the left side down; the backward direction chains the\n"
"right side down.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"A homomorphism В§27 is injective iff В§28 is trivial.\n"
"The kernel is the obstruction to injectivity: elements that collapse\n"
"together under В§29 differ by a kernel element.\"*\n"
"\n"
"**Important**: this equivalence depends on В§30 being a *homomorphism*.\n"
"For an arbitrary function, having only one preimage of В§31 (or В§32)\n"
"does not imply injectivity. The homomorphism property вҖ” В§33 вҖ”\n"
"is what connects the kernel to global injectivity.\n"
"\n"
"Dually, just as В§34 means В§35 is injective,\n"
"В§36 means В§37 is surjective. The kernel measures\n"
"information *destroyed*; the range measures information *reached*.\n"
"\n"
"Looking further ahead: the first isomorphism theorem will make this\n"
"precise вҖ” В§38, so the kernel is exactly the\n"
"\"redundancy\" that must be collapsed to recover the image.\n"
"\n"
"What's next: you'll practice these skills under varied settings in\n"
"the problem set, then meet *normal* subgroups вҖ” a property that\n"
"every kernel automatically has."
msgstr ""

