#: Game.Levels.CosetBasics.L09_Boss
msgid "You proved that В§0 is an equivalence relation on В§1.\n"
"This partitions В§2 into disjoint **left cosets** of В§3.\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *Define В§4 iff В§5. Reflexive: В§6.\n"
"Symmetric: if В§7, then В§8.\n"
"Transitive: if В§9 and В§10, then\n"
"В§11.*\n"
"\n"
"This equivalence relation is exactly the one that defines the quotient\n"
"В§12. When В§13 is a **normal** subgroup, В§14 becomes a group вҖ”\n"
"that's the quotient group construction you'll reach after studying\n"
"normality. Without normality, the equivalence classes exist but the\n"
"natural multiplication В§15 fails вҖ” the result depends\n"
"on which representatives you pick, not just which cosets.\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: There are also *right* cosets В§16. In a\n"
"non-abelian group, the left coset В§17 and the right coset В§18 can be\n"
"different sets. For example, in В§19 with В§20 and\n"
"В§21: the left coset В§22 but the right\n"
"coset В§23. A subgroup where left and right cosets\n"
"always agree is called **normal**.\n"
"\n"
"Proof moves learned:\n"
"- **Coset-membership unfold**: В§24 reduces В§25\n"
"  to В§26\n"
"- **Coset-equality move**: В§27 reduces В§28 to\n"
"  В§29\n"
"- **Inverse-flip**: В§30 via В§31 then\n"
"  В§32\n"
"- **Insert-cancel**: В§33 via В§34\n"
"  then В§35"
msgstr ""

