#: Game.Levels.GroupTutorial
msgid "Welcome to your first world: **The Group Tutorial**.\n"
"\n"
"A **group** is a set В§0 with a binary operation В§1, an identity element В§2,\n"
"and an inverse operation В§3. Groups capture the idea of reversible\n"
"transformations вҖ” rotations of a shape, permutations of a list, symmetries\n"
"of a molecule.\n"
"\n"
"A group must satisfy three axioms:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Associativity**: В§4\n"
"2. **Right identity**: В§5\n"
"3. **Right inverse**: В§6\n"
"\n"
"From these three, two useful consequences follow automatically:\n"
"\n"
"4. **Left identity**: В§7\n"
"5. **Left inverse**: В§8\n"
"\n"
"We'll use all five as tools in this world. In the next world, you'll see\n"
"why (4) and (5) follow from (1)вҖ“(3).\n"
"\n"
"In Lean and Mathlib, these are the theorems В§9, В§10, В§11,\n"
"В§12, and В§13.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, you'll learn to use each axiom one at a time, then combine them\n"
"in multi-step proofs using В§14 blocks.\n"
"\n"
"**Your goal**: by Level 8, you'll prove from these five axioms alone that\n"
"\n"
"В§15\n"
"\n"
"**Notation warning**: In Lean, multiplication is *left-associated*. That means\n"
"В§16 is the same as В§17, **not** В§18. You'll need\n"
"В§19 to move the parentheses.\n"
"\n"
"You already know В§20 and В§21 from the Natural Number Game. Those are the\n"
"only tactics you need here вҖ” plus a new one called В§22 that you'll meet in\n"
"Level 6.\n"
"\n"
"Let's begin."
msgstr ""

