#: Game.Levels.HomDef.L05_MapInv
msgid "Together, В§0, В§1, and В§2 say that a homomorphism\n"
"\"commutes\" with all group operations:\n"
"\n"
"| Lemma | Statement |\n"
"|-------|-----------|\n"
"| В§3 | В§4 |\n"
"| В§5 | В§6 |\n"
"| В§7 | В§8 |\n"
"\n"
"The key insight: only В§9 is an axiom. В§10 and В§11\n"
"are *consequences*. If you tried the alternative proof\n"
"В§12, you derived the result\n"
"using only В§13 and В§14 вҖ” the same **hom-property move**\n"
"you used in the last level.\n"
"\n"
"Some concrete examples of homomorphisms:\n"
"- The **identity map** В§15 (sends every element to itself)\n"
"- The **trivial map** В§16 sending every element to В§17\n"
"- The **squaring map** in a commutative group (you'll build this soon)\n"
"\n"
"The trivial map sends *everything* to В§18, so its kernel is all of В§19 вҖ”\n"
"the maximally non-injective case. You'll explore kernels in the next world."
msgstr ""

